I'm taking part of #ExcelsoProjectHero2
I have a passion in the field of pastry and I learned pastry by self-taught through browsing various recipes or reading cookbooks. Cooking is not an easy thing, it takes patience and willingness to keep trying and learning from every failure experienced. Sometimes when I bake a cake the cake fails and does not work out as I expected. As a human, I feel sad and disappointed but I try to rise from the failure and make it as an experience to bake better. I have a dream to open a cake shop but the struggle to realize the ideals is not easy and take more efforts. I will struggle to make my dream comes true altough I totally do not study in the culinary field. Why am I doing this? The biggest reason is I want to work and live with my passion.
#ExcelsoCoffee

I'm taking part of #ExcelsoProjectHero2
Recently we celebrated Indonesia's 72nd Independence Day on 17th August 2017. Independence is synonymous with the word of struggle. The struggle in the past means the reciprocal of Indonesian society with bamboo spikes, but in these days of reform the struggle means building nation of Indonesia.
As a student, society expect us to be human beings bearer changes, movers and successors of the nation. I am struggling to realize every society's dreams by studying earnestly, exploring ideas, knowledge, and opening the window of my insights.
The struggle of the past and present is different but the spirit of the blazing past is still within me.
#ExcelsoCoffee
